<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Which Dictionary Do They Use?</h2>

<p>The dictionary a checker uses determines what it accepts. This is the single most important factor in choosing a tool:</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-3">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-400 mb-1">SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words)</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">~280,000 words. Used internationally (UK, Australia, most of the world). The most permissive official Scrabble dictionary. If a word is valid anywhere, SOWPODS likely includes it.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-400 mb-1">TWL (Tournament Word List)</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">~187,000 words. Used in North America (US, Canada, Thailand, Israel). Stricter — excludes many words that SOWPODS accepts. The standard for most online platforms.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/10">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-1">ENABLE (Words With Friends)</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">~173,000 words. Used exclusively by Words With Friends. A completely separate list — some words valid here aren't in SOWPODS/TWL, and vice versa.</p>
  </div>
</div>

